article.headline: Mercer 77, North Florida 71
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Will Emerson scored 19 points, including back-to-back baskets with six minutes remaining to break the game's sixth tie, as Mercer defeated North Florida 77-71 on Sunday in an Atlantic Sun Conference game. Emerson scored 13 second-half points, hitting a layup and a 3-pointer on consecutive possessions to snap a 58-58 tie and fuel a quick 7-0 run by the Bears (9-16, 7-11). The burst gave Mercer the lead for good and helped it win for the fourth time in five games. North Florida (6-21, 3-16) sliced its deficit to two points twice in the final four minutes but could never get closer. The Ospreys got a career-high 22 points from Chris Timberlake, while Alain Laroche added 14. Rashad Williams posted his fifth career double-double with 11 points and 10 rebounds, but it wasn't enough to prevent the Ospreys from losing their sixth straight game. North Florida led 35-30 at halftime in a game that featured nine lead changes and six ties. The Ospreys shot 41 percent for the game, while Mercer shot 50 percent. North Florida won the rebounding battle, 37-28.
